==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*kwinō-'', from Indo-European ''*gʷena-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[cwena]] (Dutch [[kween]] ‘barren cow’), Old High German [[quena]], Old Norse [[kvenna]] (Swedish [[kvinna]]), Gothic [[𐌵𐌹𐌽𐍉]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[γυνη]], Slavic ''*ženā'' (Old Church Slavonic [[жена]], Russian [[жена]]), Old Irish [[ben]] (Welsh [[benyw]]), Albanian [[zonjë]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'kwene/

